      <hedline>
        <hl1>NORTEL BUYING EQUIPMENT MAKER</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Nortel Networks agrees to buy Sonoma Systems, privately held maker of high-speed data devices, in stock deal valued at $540 million (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Nortel Networks said yesterday that it had agreed to buy Sonoma Systems, a privately held maker of high-speed data devices, in a stock deal valued at $540 million. Under the terms of the deal, about $60 million worth of shares is payable only if Sonoma meets certain unspecified goals in the year after the deal closes.</p>
      </block>
